cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CE 

The paper deals with the problem of influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis of social networks and their properties. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and models to solve the problem, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses the scalability and efficiency of the proposed algorithms, which falls under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical proofs to establish the complexity of the problem, which makes cs.TH (Theoretical Computer Science) a possible category as well.
